race.comment: ONEFORIAN (5) led unexpectedly and was much to good resuming in this grade and distance at Wagga. Draws inside and may employ the same tactics today. He's been further improved by the Olive yard and can go on with the job. BROOKLYN LIGHTS (8) raced forward and spaced a CL1 field at Moruya. He then led under a low weight when narrowly beaten in a CL3 at Rosehill. That's good form but from the outside barrier will need a judicious ride from the in-form Budler. RILEYCAT (11) has been racing in town and is better suited. Has a handy 2kg claim and finally draws a low barrier. Has ability and keep onside. CEREMONIOUS (4) resumed with a win in a Cowra CL3 and expect that to stack up. Will have come on and will be in the frame with average luck in the run.
